        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-23325" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-23325" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>The Better Angels of our Nature is probably the book I recommend the most to anyone. I picked it up initially because the premise seemed very interesting, but as I kept reading, I was astonished at what I learned. Not only does it exhaustively argue its point so well that only the most hardened cynic would try to disagree, it culminates in what almost seems like a &#8220;how to guide&#8221; for humanity. Couldn&#8217;t think of a more relevant book for a collection with this goal. If it doesn&#8217;t make it into the collection, I would be surprised and disappointed.</p>
</div>
        </div>

